 bridge you to become a fully devoted follower of Christ. Select one class this session and then jump into the next class the following quarter.<strong> </strong>&nbsp;Each class builds on the next to help you look a little more like Jesus and make Portland Christian Center your home.</p><p style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://secure.accessacs.com/access/eventlogin.aspx?id=59AoOrBpAJ3TYSSyEhBOWA==&amp;site=1233&amp;ReturnUrl=events%2fwz_people.aspx&amp;ChurchID=3183&amp;EventID=51106&amp;sn=1233" class="button">Register Here</a></p><p><a href="#Schedule">Curious about the schedule of the day or what time dinner is served? Click here &gt;&gt;</a></p><p><img title="GRAPHIC : LOGO : Connect 101 : GIF" alt="GRAPHIC : LOGO : Connect 101 : GIF" src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1364395&amp;fileName=graphic--logo--connect-101--gif-0-0-317-80.gif" width="317" height="80"></p><h4>CONNECT 101: CONNECT WITH MY CHURCH FAMILY</h4><h5>Taught by Pastor Ray Noah, Board Members, and Others</h5><p>CONNECT 101 is designed to clearly explain God&rsquo;s hand on Portland Christian Center and plans for the future. You&rsquo;ll learn about our beliefs, our statements of purpose, and our church&rsquo;s strategy and structure. You&rsquo;ll also hear about the history of our church, how the five biblical purposes are necessary to fulfilling God&rsquo;s calling for your life and how you can play a part in what God is up to at PCC. At the end of CONNECT 101, you are invited, but not required to become members.</p><hr><p><img title="GRAPHIC : LOGO : Connect 201 : GIF" alt="GRAPHIC : LOGO : Connect 201 : GIF" src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1364611&amp;fileName=graphic--logo--connect-201--gif-0-0-317-80.gif" width="317" height="80"></p><h4 class="clr">CONNECT 201:&nbsp;CONNECT WITH HABITS OF SIMPLE FAITH</h4><h5>Taught by Pastor Caleb Bryant and Pastor Rod Rider</h5><p>CONNECT 201 focuses on establishing habits that promote healthy spiritual growth and maturity. We will take a look at the growth process of your life with Christ and how to take the next step to become more like Christ. Special attention is given to understanding the what, why, when, and how of four core habits:&nbsp; Prayer, Daily Time With God, Tithing, and Fellowship.&nbsp; This inspiring class is excellent for those who are looking for practical ways to grow or refresh their walk with Christ.</p><hr><p><img title="GRAPHIC : LOGO : Connect 301 : GIF" alt="GRAPHIC : LOGO : Connect 301 : GIF" src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1364619&amp;fileName=graphic--logo--connect-301--gif-0-0-317-80.gif" width="317" height="80"></p><h4 class="clr">CONNECT 301:&nbsp;CONNECT WITH MY LIFE DESIGN BY LEARNING MY S.H.A.P.E.</h4><h5>Taught by Pastor Joel &amp; Amy Slater, and Others</h5><p>In CONNECT 301, through diagnostic tools, activities, and discussion you will develop a personal understanding of God&rsquo;s workmanship in your life by learning your S.H.A.P.E. (Spiritual Gifts, Heart, Abilities, Personality, Experiences).&nbsp; Special attention is directed towards finding ways to use your gifts (S.H.A.P.E.) to impact the Kingdom of God in profound ways as you express your gifts and talents for the glory of God. We've been told this class is life-changing!</p><hr><p><img title="GRAPHIC : LOGO : Connect 401 : GIF" alt="GRAPHIC : LOGO : Connect 401 : GIF" src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1364621&amp;fileName=graphic--logo--connect-401--gif-0-0-317-80.gif" width="317" height="80"></p><h4 class="clr">&nbsp;CONNECT 401:&nbsp;CONNECT WITH MY LIFE MISSION AND SHARE MY STORY</h4><h5>Taught by Pastor Linda Noah</h5><p>IN CONNECT 401 you&rsquo;ll discover your life mission and how through your life story God is at work to help you impact the world. In this class you will (1) Develop a personal perspective of the Gospel message; (2) Develop your personal story and how God has been at work all along in your life; (3) Build confidence in sharing your story; (4) And, begin building a framework for developing a Life Plan.&nbsp; Complete CONNECT 301 before attending this class so that you understand your gifts and talents and can talk with some knowledge about them.</p><hr><h3>THE CONNECT EXPERIENCE FOR KIDS!</h3><p>Pastor Phil Hahn has an amazing experience just for kids at Portland Christian Center. If you are coming to our Connect Experience for Adults please consider bringing your children with you. We plan on learning what it means to be a kid following after Jesus! This program is available for children ages three months - 5th grade.</p><hr><p><a class="button" href="https://secure.accessacs.com/access/eventlogin.aspx?id=NA7SmJyGM47xNfUOp/r0lg==&amp;site=1233&amp;ReturnUrl=events%2fwz_people.aspx&amp;ChurchID=3183&amp;EventID=43394&amp;sn=1233">Register Here</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><a id="Schedule"></a>Schedule:</h4><table border="0"><tbody><tr><td>2:30 PM</td><td>Doors Open / Nursery Opens</td></tr><tr><td>3:00 PM</td><td>Session 1 in Class Groups</td></tr><tr><td>5:00 PM</td><td>Community Dinner (complimentary)</td></tr><tr><td>5:45 PM</td><td>Session 2 in Class Groups</td></tr><tr><td>7:00 PM</td><td>Dismissal</td></tr></tbody></table><hr><h3><a href="http://f049e6c6bc51d6086828-1f3d9bf827f6f62072870f1ea348709c.r40.cf2.rackcdn.com/uploaded/g/0e2269441_1372894651_graphic--staff-photo--linda-noah-crop.jpg"><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=390278&amp;fileName=graphic--staff-photo--linda-noah--001--jpg-0-0-120-168.jpg" width="120" height="168" alt="GRAPHIC : STAFF PHOTO : Linda Noah : 001 : JPG" title="GRAPHIC : STAFF PHOTO : Linda Noah : 001 : JPG" style="vertical-align: top;"></a>Pastoral Oversight</h3><p class="class-intstructor-bio"><b>LINDA NOAH</b>&nbsp;is part of the pastoral team at Portland Christian Center and is one of our teaching pastors. As a member of the Senior Leadership Team she has oversight over Adult Education (Life Learning), Communications, Hilltop Preschool &amp; Kindergarten, Women's Ministry and Petros Network.</p><p class="class-intstructor-bio">Linda has a deep love for the Word of God and an ability to make it practical for the learner. In addition to her ministry background Linda is a certified coach and business/leadership consultant. She is also a certified Transformational Leadership facilitator. Linda is married to our Lead Pastor, Pastor Ray Noah and has two adult children and one son-in-law, Danielle, Ashley and Vik.</p><div class="clr">&nbsp;</div><p>Follow/Contact LINDA:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=631758095&amp;ref=ts" class="facebook">Facebook</a>&nbsp;<a href="http://twitter.com/LindaNoah" class="twitter" target="_blank">Twitter</a>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/lindanoah" class="linkedin" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a>&nbsp;<a href="mailto:lnoah@pcctoday.com" class="email" target="_blank">Email</a></p>